==English==
===Etymology===
Sanskrit ''[[अद्बैत]] (advaita)'', Lit: "not two."

===Noun===
'''Advaitism'''

# The "non-dualist" school of [[Vedanta]] founded by the 8th century Indian philosopher Sankaracharya.  Comparable views are held by the Sufi ''Wujudiyyah.''

